<span class="name"><a name="1549"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#4:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Tsunae</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=1549&amp;sid=ae7fea07f475d0891ab02a16d0afeb59#1549"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Mon Jun 10, 2002 2:35 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
	<span class="gensmall">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;----</span><br>

<span class="postbody">Logging off didn't help, but I found a work around!!
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
What was happening was the skill WAS being assigned to the button.  The button caption just wasn't sticking.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
SO...and my Summon Warder is assigned to Skill #4...I made a hotbutton like so:
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
/hotbutton get.pet 8 /do 4
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
where &quot;get.pet&quot; is the label, 8 is the text color (gray), and &quot;/do 4&quot; launches the 4th skill.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Whoohoo!
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Thanks for letting me think out loud.    Tsunae Clouddancer
<br />
Level 51 Druid
<br />
Soulfire EQ Game Leader
